  "prompt": "Why Democracy index 2012 assigned India to flawed Democracy category?",
  "response": "The Democracy Index, published by the Economist Intelligence Unit (EIU), categorized India as a \"flawed democracy\" in 2012 due to several key factors:\n\n1. Electoral Process and Pluralism:\n- Concerns about the fairness and transparency of electoral processes\n- Issues with electoral participation and voter representation\n- Challenges in ensuring free and fair elections\n\n2. Government Functioning:\n- Inefficiencies in government performance\n- Bureaucratic hurdles\n- Slow decision-making processes\n- Challenges in implementing policies effectively\n\n3. Political Participation:\n- Limited political engagement from certain segments of society\n- Low voter turnout in some regions\n- Uneven political representation\n\n4. Political Culture:\n- Presence of political corruption\n- Challenges in maintaining democratic values\n- Gaps in political accountability\n\n5. Civil Liberties:\n- Restrictions on individual freedoms\n- Challenges in ensuring equal rights\n- Issues with press freedom\n- Limitations on freedom of expression\n\nThese factors collectively contributed to India being classified as a \"flawed democracy\" in the 2012 Democracy Index, indicating that while democratic institutions existed, significant improvements were needed in various aspects of democratic governance.",
